            <h2 class="section-title mt-4 text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.01em]">
              What “integrity-bound records” support
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slateblue leading-relaxed measure">
              In institutional review, the question is often not “Is the output correct?” but “Can a specific event be verified as authentic, unaltered, and generated under defined controls?”
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8">
            <div class="border hairline p-6 no-rounded reveal">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slateblue/90">[CORE PROPERTIES]</div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-slateblue leading-relaxed">
                <li><span class="font-semibold">Authenticity:</span> whether a record can be attributed to a system and time window under controlled operation.</li>
                <li><span class="font-semibold">Integrity:</span> whether a record is tamper-evident (hash + signature over a canonical form).</li>
                <li><span class="font-semibold">Contemporaneousness:</span> whether a record is generated systematically near the time of the event.</li>
                <li><span class="font-semibold">Repeatability of structure:</span> whether the record format is stable enough for later review and verification workflows.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 border hairline p-6 no-rounded reveal">
              <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slateblue/90">[BOUNDARY]</div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-slateblue leading-relaxed">
                <li>NADIR does not decide admissibility. Courts, regulators, or authorized institutions make admissibility determinations.</li>
                <li>NADIR does not validate the correctness of model outputs; it preserves integrity-bound records under defined policy scope.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Mechanics (table + protocol, not “same 3 cards”) -->
    <section class="border-t hairline">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-20">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-10">
